The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Ride kills mother
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Ride kills mother
                            
	Bangalore, June 30: A young mother was flung to her death during an amusement park ride today but her three-year-old daughter survived, landing in the arms of a spectator.        
	Ayesha Razak was in her seat in a Tora Tora  a moving platform of a dozen boxes  when the safety handle of the box she was in gave way.        
	Police said the 24-year-old was flung off the ride, then in full momentum. Her head smashed into the railing, killing her on the spot.        
	The police have arrested Suresh Chandra Shukla, the owner of Fun Style Amusements, who runs the rides at Bal Bhavan, a popular childrens park.                                                                                                                                                                         
